{{1982–83 ECAC South men's basketball standings}}
The '''1983 [[Colonial Athletic Association Men's Basketball Tournament|ECAC South Men's Basketball Tournament]]''' (now known as the '''Colonial Athletic Association Men's Basketball Tournament''') was held March 10–12 at the [[Robins Center]] in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. The champion, {{cbb link|1982|sex=men|team=James Madison Dukes|school=James Madison University|title=James Madison}}, received an automatic bid to the [[1983 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1983 NCAA Tournament]]; it was JMU's third-ever NCAA Tournament berth. The runner-up, [[1982–83 William & Mary Tribe men's basketball team|William & Mary]], received an at-large bid to the [[1983 National Invitation Tournament]]; it was W&M's first-ever postseason berth of any kind.

